	<event name="SUMMON_TC_STORAGE">
		<text>Contact the Trash Compactor? (WARNING - HIGH RISK, HIGH REWARD)</text>
		<choice req="TC_DEAD" lvl="0" max_group="3" hidden="false" blue="false">
			<text>Yes. (Recommended Sector: 1+)</text>
			<event>
			<text>You send out a signal displaying the scrap using the transmitter. Shortly after, your map recieves coordinates of a ship's location. </text>
				<item_modify>
					<item type="scrap" min="-10" max="-10"/>
				</item_modify>
				<quest event="ENCOUNTER_TC1"/>
			</event>
		</choice>
		<choice req="TC_DEAD" lvl="1" max_group="3" hidden="false" blue="false">
			<text>Yes. (Recommended Sector: 2+)</text>
			<event>
				<text>You use some fuel and a long range transmission missile as well as your scrap. Shortly after, your map recieves coordinates of a ship's location - most likely the Scrappers from earlier. What do they want from you? </text>
				<item_modify>
					<item type="scrap" min="-20" max="-20"/>
					<item type="fuel" min="-1" max="-1"/>
				</item_modify>
				<quest event="ENCOUNTER_TC2"/>
			</event>
		</choice>
		<choice  req="TC_DEAD" lvl="2" max_group="3" hidden="false" blue="false">
			<text>Yes. (Recommended Sector: 4+)</text>
			<event>
			<text>You send out a heavy cargo drone with the scrap. There must be more of these Scrappers, because you received another signal! Prey for you to hunt... </text>
				<item_modify>
					<item type="scrap" min="-15" max="-15"/>
					<item type="fuel" min="-1" max="-1"/>
					<item type="drones" min="-1" max="-1"/>
				</item_modify>
				<quest event="ENCOUNTER_TC3"/>
			</event>
		</choice>
		<choice  req="TC_DEAD" lvl="3" max_group="3" hidden="false" blue="false">
			<text>Yes. (Recommended Sector: 5+)</text>
			<event>
			<text>You teleport as much as scrap as you can using the transmitter. The same song and dance as before - signal, Scrappers, murder. Fun. </text>
				<item_modify>
					<item type="scrap" min="-20" max="-20"/>
					<item type="fuel" min="-1" max="-1"/>
					<item type="drones" min="-2" max="-2"/>
				</item_modify>
				<quest event="ENCOUNTER_TC4"/>
			</event>
		</choice>
		<choice  req="TC_DEAD" lvl="4" max_group="3" hidden="false" blue="false">
			<text>Yes. (Recommended Sector: 6+)</text>
			<event>
			<text>You manage to create and fully fuel a scrap transport pod, attracting the attention of a heavily armed, highly dangerous Scrapper ship. </text>
				<item_modify>
					<item type="scrap" min="-30" max="-30"/>
					<item type="fuel" min="-1" max="-1"/>
					<item type="drones" min="-2" max="-2"/>
				</item_modify>
				<quest event="ENCOUNTER_TC5"/>
			</event>
		</choice>
		<choice  req="TC_DEAD" lvl="5" max_group="3" hidden="false" blue="false">
			<text>Yes. (Recommended Sector: 8+)</text>
			<event>
			<text>You send out a signal displaying the scrap using the transmitter. Shortly after, your map recieves coordinates of a ship's location - most likely the Scrapper ship from earlier. </text>
				<item_modify>
					<item type="scrap" min="-40" max="-40"/>
					<item type="fuel" min="-1" max="-1"/>
					<item type="drones" min="-3" max="-3"/>
				</item_modify>
				<quest event="ENCOUNTER_TC6"/>
			</event>
		</choice>
		<choice  req="TC_DEAD" lvl="6" max_group="3" hidden="false" blue="false">
			<text>Yes.</text>
			<event>
			<text>You send out a signal displaying the scrap using the transmitter.
				But nobody came.</text>
				<choice>
					<text>Continue...</text>
					<event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
				</choice>
			</event>
		</choice>
		<choice req="tc_quest_completed" lvl="1" max_group="4" hidden="false" blue="true">
			<text>Send out a signal using multiversal frequencies.</text>
			<event>
			<text>Which signal do you want to send out? 
			(These enemies are very strong and are more focused on boarding. Reccomended to be fought in S5+)</text>
				<choice req="tc_rosegold_defeated" lvl="0" max_lvl="0" blue="false">
					<text>A Rosegold one. (Recommended Sector: 6+)</text>
					<event>
						<text>You teleport the materials using the transmitter. Now we wait. </text>
						<item_modify>
							<item type="scrap" min="-30" max="-30"/>
							<item type="drones" min="-3" max="-3"/>
						</item_modify>
						<quest event="ENCOUNTER_TC_ROSEGOLD"/>
					</event>
				</choice>
				<choice req="tc_rosegold_defeated" lvl="1" hidden="true" blue="false">
					<text>You have defeated the Rosegold Trash Compactor.</text>
					<event load="OPTION_INVALID"/>
				</choice>
				<choice req="tc_golden_defeated" lvl="0" max_lvl="0" blue="false">
					<text>A Golden one. (Recommended Sector: 6+)</text>
					<event>
						<text>You teleport the materials using the transmitter. Now we wait. </text>
						<item_modify>
							<item type="scrap" min="-30" max="-30"/>
							<item type="fuel" min="-3" max="-3"/>
						</item_modify>
						<quest event="ENCOUNTER_TC_GOLDEN"/>
					</event>
				</choice>
				<choice req="tc_golden_defeated" lvl="1" hidden="true" blue="false">
					<text>You have defeated the Golden Trash Compactor.</text>
					<event load="OPTION_INVALID"/>
				</choice>
				<choice req="tc_adamantine_defeated" lvl="0" max_lvl="0" blue="false">
					<text>An Adamantine one. (Recommended Sector: 6+)</text>
					<event>
						<text>You teleport the materials using the transmitter. Now we wait. </text>
						<item_modify>
							<item type="scrap" min="-30" max="-30"/>
							<item type="missiles" min="-3" max="-3"/>
						</item_modify>
						<quest event="ENCOUNTER_TC_ADAMANTINE"/>
					</event>
				</choice>
				<choice req="tc_adamantine_defeated" lvl="1" hidden="true" blue="false">
					<text>You have defeated the Adamantine Trash Compactor.</text>
					<event load="OPTION_INVALID"/>
				</choice>
				<choice req="ALL_ELEMENTS_DEFEATED" blue="true">
					<text>???</text>
					<event>
						<text>You didn't even transmit anything but a signal appears on your map. Guess we know what to do now.</text>
						<quest event="ENCOUNTER_TC_ZOG"/>
					</event>
				</choice>
				<choice>
					<text>Nevermind.</text>
					<event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
				</choice>
			</event>
		</choice>
		<choice  req="tc_zog_met" lvl="2" max_lvl="2" max_group="5" hidden="false" blue="true">
			<text>Contact The Architect. (Recommended Sector: 8+)</text>
			<event>
			<text>You send out a signal displaying the scrap using the transmitter. Shortly after, your map recieves coordinates of a ship's location. Here we go.</text>
				<quest event="ENCOUNTER_TC_ZOG_FIGHT"/>
			</event>
		</choice>
		<choice  req="tc_quest2_completed" lvl="1" max_group="6" hidden="false" blue="true">
			<text>Fight the superboss.</text>
			<event>
				<text>This is an entirely optional incredibly hard boss that wasn't designed to be beatable. I don't even know if it's possible to beat. Pressing continue will send you straight into the fight.

				You have been warned.</text>
				<choice>
					<text>Continue.</text>
					<event load="ENCOUNTER_TC_ZOG_SUPER"/>
				</choice>
				<choice>
					<text>Nevermind.</text>
					<event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
				</choice>
			</event>
		</choice>
		<!--
		<choice req="pilot" lvl="1" max_group="4" hidden="false" blue="true">
			<text>There's a rotary phone hanging on the side of the machine...</text>
			<event>
			<text>...so you pick the receiver up. It seems that you didn't have to dial anything. A rough, metallic voice picks up. "Hey. You're an. Uhm." Papers are being flipped next to the other line's receiver. "Right. Sorry. Renegade. My name's TRACKER, I'm a... freelancer. I need your help. Come and meet me." The receiver is filled with static again. He hung up.</text>
