	<FTL> <!--DESTROYED-->
	<event name="TC1_DESTROY">
		<text>Who even were these guys? You blew them all to pieces by baiting them with scrap, and yet, you have a feeling this is not over yet... Perhaps there's more of them somewhere else...
			While searching through the remains of the ship, you find a dying member of its crew, clutching an intact weapon it seemingly stripped from right from the hull. It seems like they're nibbling on it.
			You can snatch the weapon from them, take them both with you, or leave them to die.
		</text>
		<playMusic/>
		<autoReward level="HIGH">stuff</autoReward>
		<choice>
			<text>Snatch the weapon.</text>
			<event>
				<text>You chose to take the functional weapon, leaving the crew member to its fate.</text>
				<weapon name="TC_SHOTGUN_BOMB"/>
			</event>
		</choice>
		<choice>
			<text>Allow the crew member to eat the weapon.</text>
			<event>
				<text>You promise the scrapper additional scrap for work and a home onboard a non-destroyed ship. After beaming aboard, they quickly finish the weapon, revitalizing themselves.</text>
				<crewMember amount="1" class="scrapper"/>
			</event>
		</choice>
		<choice>
			<text>Spend some extra time salvaging.</text>
				<event>
					<text>You instead spend some extra time salvaging and beam away without looking back.
						The wounded scrapper watches you beam away, who knows if it will live or die floating forever, lost in space wreckage. How rude. 
					</text>
					<item_modify>
						<item type="fuel" min="1" max="6"/>
						<item type="scrap" min="1" max="15"/>
						<item type="drones" min="1" max="6"/>
						<item type="missiles" min="1" max="6"/>
					</item_modify>
				</event>
		</choice>
		<hiddenAug>TC_DEAD</hiddenAug>
		<hiddenAug>TC1_DEAD</hiddenAug>
	</event>

