		<text>The Fleet ship lays broken before your ship. With the other ships scattering in panic, you can now quickly scan the remains and get a few materials.
			In the wreckage, you find a seemingly advanced piece of equipment that easily integrates itself in your systems. You notice additional options in your onboard lab.
			While searching through the remains of the ship, you find yet another dying member of its crew, this one looks much larger than the last two you found. You're not shocked to find them nervously eating an advanced flak cannon. 
			You can snatch the weapon from them, take them both with you, or leave them to die.		
		</text>
		<playMusic/>
		<autoReward level="HIGH">stuff</autoReward>
		<choice>
			<text>Snatch the weapon.</text>
			<event>
				<text>You chose to take the functional weapon, leaving the crew member to its fate.</text>
				<weapon name="TC_SHOTGUN_LEAD"/>
			</event>
		</choice>
		<choice>
			<text>Allow the crew member to eat the weapon.</text>
			<event>
				<text>You promise the scrapper additional scrap for work and a home onboard a non-destroyed ship. After beaming aboard, they quickly finish the weapon, revitalizing themselves.</text>
				<crewMember amount="1" class="scrapper_heavy"/>
			</event>
		</choice>
		<choice>
			<text>Spend some extra time salvaging.</text>
				<event>
					<text>You instead spend some extra time salvaging and beam away without looking back.
						The wounded scrapper watches you beam away, who knows if it will live or die floating forever, lost in space wreckage. How rude. 
					</text>
					<item_modify>
						<item type="fuel" min="3" max="9"/>
						<item type="scrap" min="25" max="45"/>
						<item type="drones" min="3" max="9"/>
						<item type="missiles" min="3" max="9"/>
					</item_modify>
				</event>
		</choice>
		<hiddenAug>TC_DEAD</hiddenAug>
		<hiddenAug>TC3_DEAD</hiddenAug>
		<hiddenAug>ADVANCED_SCRAP</hiddenAug>
	</event>

	<event name="TC4_DESTROY">
		<text>The Scrapper's ship is now torn to shreds and the Kestrel Miner hails you. "That's fantastic, we always appreciate help! CHEEESE! BEAM THEM, uhhhhh... THE BLUEPRINTS FOR OUR SHIP! AND THAT GARBAGE WEAPON THAT LANCER MADE!".
			While searching through the wreckage of the ship, you find a wounded Trash Eater clutching an advanced Flak Cannon. You're familiar with how wounded scrappers will eat weapons to survive, but the Trash Eater just holds it, staring at you.
			You can offer him a position on your ship though it may cost you.
		</text>
		<playMusic/>
		<autoReward level="HIGH">stuff</autoReward>
		<choice>
			<text>Snatch the weapon.</text>
			<event>
				<text>You chose to take the functional weapon, leaving the crew member to its fate.</text>
				<weapon name="TC_SCRAPFLAK"/>
			</event>
		</choice>
		<choice>
			<text>Offer the Trash Eater a position on your crew.</text>
