	<FTL>
	<eventList name="SCRAP_COMPACT">
		<event load="SCRAP_COMPACT_FAIL"/>
		<event load="SCRAP_COMPACT_FAIL"/>
		<event load="SCRAP_COMPACT_FAIL"/>
		<event load="SCRAP_COMPACT_SUCCESS"/>
		<event load="SCRAP_COMPACT_SUCCESS"/>
		<event load="SCRAP_COMPACT_SUCCESS_BETTER"/>
		<event load="SCRAP_COMPACT_SUCCESS_BETTER2"/>
	</eventList>

	<event name="SCRAP_COMPACT_FAIL">
	<text>You attempt to configure the machine in order to create something useful, but after a few minutes of bootlooping, it seems all you've made is a protogen figurine. Or in other words, scrap.</text>
	<item_modify>
		<item type="scrap" min="25" max="35"/>
	</item_modify>
	</event>

	<event name="SCRAP_COMPACT_SUCCESS">
	<text>You fire up the machine. After some complicated troubleshooting and every single screen on it turning blue, you manage to get it to create something. A Flak II! How... competent.</text>
	<weapon name="SHOTGUN_2"/>
	</event>

	<event name="SCRAP_COMPACT_SUCCESS_BETTER">
	<text>You've created... something hellish. The Compactor is visbily smoking. Let's get the enemy ships on fire too.</text>
	<weapon name="TC_SHOTGUN_HELL"/>
	</event>

	<event name="SCRAP_COMPACT_SUCCESS_BETTER2">
	<text>The Compactor throws up several errors at you, most of them being 719: MATERIAL INCORRECT. A loud ping signals that something has indeed been created though...</text>
	<weapon name="TC_SCRAPFLAK"/>
	</event>
	</FTL>

<!--/////////////////////////////////////////ENCOUNTER TEXT//////////////////////////////////////////////-->

<event name="ENCOUNTER_TC1">
	<preventQuest/>
	<preventFleet/>
	<aggressive>2</aggressive>
<text>You've arrived at the coordinates, only to be met with the same Lanius ship from before. This looks like a trap, but they aren't attacking you, nor are their weapons on... yet.</text>
<beaconType id="map_icon_trash" global="true">
	<color r="110" g="32" b="9" a="1.0"/>
	<unvisitedTooltip>C0ME aND GET It</unvisitedTooltip>
	<visitedTooltip>Explored location. Nothing left of interest.</visitedTooltip>
	<undiscoveredTooltip>W3 ArE HeRE StILL</undiscoveredTooltip>
</beaconType>
<ship load="TC_TRASH_COMPACTOR1" hostile="false"/>
<choice req="TC1_DEAD" lvl="0" hidden="true" blue="false" max_group="0">
	<text>Attempt to hail them.</text>
	<event>
		<text>The strange lanius ship descends in your view, scoops up the scrap you sent them and attacks!</text>
		<ship hostile="true"/>
		<choice hidden="true">
			<text>Prepare for battle!</text>
			<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
		</choice>
	</event>
</choice>
<choice req="TC1_DEAD" lvl="1" hidden="true" blue="false" max_group="0">
	<text>Weird deja vu, but you feel like you've done this all before.</text>
	<event load="OPTION_INVALID"/>
</choice>
<choice req="pilot" lvl="1" max_group="998" blue="false" hidden="true">
	<text>Attempt to sneak away from the Lanius.</text>
	<event>
		<text>You manage to leave succesfully, with the opportunity of doing something on-board.</text>
		<choice>
			<text>Do something onboard the ship.</text>
			<event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
		</choice>
		<choice>
			<text>Do nothing.</text>
			<event/>
		</choice>
	</event>
</choice>
</event>

<event name="ENCOUNTER_TC2">
	<preventQuest/>
	<preventFleet/>
	<aggressive>2</aggressive>
<text>You've arrived at the new coordinates. It's a ship similar to the one from earlier. It is unclear if they're the same guys from before, or if they just came out of another universe...</text>
<beaconType id="map_icon_trash" global="true">
	<color r="110" g="32" b="9" a="1.0"/>
	<unvisitedTooltip>C0ME aND GET It</unvisitedTooltip>
	<visitedTooltip>Explored location. Nothing left of interest.</visitedTooltip>
	<undiscoveredTooltip>W3 ArE HeRE StILL</undiscoveredTooltip>
</beaconType>
<ship load="TC_TRASH_COMPACTOR2" hostile="false"/>
<choice req="TC2_DEAD" lvl="0" hidden="true" blue="false" max_group="0">
	<text>Attack them.</text>
	<event>
	<text>The strange lanius ship descends in your view and powers up weapons.</text>
		<ship hostile="true"/>
		<choice hidden="true">
			<text>Prepare for battle.</text>
			<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
		</choice>
	</event>
</choice>
<choice req="TC2_DEAD" lvl="1" hidden="true" blue="false" max_group="0">
	<text>They're gone. Right? ...right?</text>
	<event load="OPTION_INVALID"/>
</choice>
<choice req="pilot" lvl="1" max_group="998" blue="false" hidden="true">
	<text>Not every fight is our fight.</text>
	<event>
		<text>You manage to sneak away by distracting the Scrappers - it seems the old "Rusting locomotives in your area" method still works.</text>
		<choice>
			<text>Do something onboard the ship.</text>
			<event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
		</choice>
		<choice>
			<text>Do nothing.</text>
			<event/>
		</choice>
	</event>
</choice>
</event>

