<event name="ENCOUNTER_TC3">
	<preventQuest/>
	<preventFleet/>
	<aggressive>2</aggressive>
	<text>Arriving at the beacon, you are met by four entire ships, all of them readying weapons against you. You won't be able to manuever away without fighting at least one ship.</text>
	<beaconType id="map_icon_trash" global="true">
        <color r="110" g="32" b="9" a="1.0"/>
        <unvisitedTooltip>C0ME aND GET It</unvisitedTooltip>
        <visitedTooltip>Explored location. Nothing left of interest.</visitedTooltip>
        <undiscoveredTooltip>W3 ArE HeRE StILL</undiscoveredTooltip>
  </beaconType>
	<choice req="TC3_DEAD" lvl="0" hidden="true" blue="false" max_group="0">
		<text>Get closer...</text>
		<event>
			<text>The four ships have you cornered - who will you attack?</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Attack the Corvette ship. </text>
				<event>
					<text>The Corvette starts powering up its weapons, detaches from the Trash fleet and takes position to fire at your ship!</text>
					<ship load="TC_SCRAPPER_CORVETTE" hostile="true"/>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Prepare for battle.</text>
						<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice>
				<text>Attack the Hunter ship. </text>
				<event>
					<text>The Hunter acquires teleporter lock-on to your ship. Get ready for intruders!</text>
					<ship load="TC_SCRAPPER_HUNTER" hostile="true"/>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Prepare for battle.</text>
						<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice>
				<text>Attack the Support ship. </text>
				<event>
					<text>The Support ship maneuvers itself close to your ship and powers up its drones!</text>
					<ship load="TC_SCRAPPER_SUPPORT" hostile="true"/>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Prepare for battle.</text>
						<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice>
				<text>Ignore the lesser ships and attack the Trash Compactor itself. </text>
				<event>
					<text>The Trash Compactor was waiting for you, seemingly having anticipated your movements. You get a garbled, badly translated hail from them: "WE not sAme UN1verse. We smMORTer thAn oTher SCrappErS, wE k1Ll uNiversE and PREZent to leader FOR eat. STANd in the w4y, Y0u, die...". These guys aren't gonna talk it out, though, as they already powered up weapons!</text>
					<ship load="TC_TRASH_COMPACTOR3" hostile="true"/>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Let's end this. Again.</text>
						<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice req="TC3_DEAD" lvl="1" hidden="true" blue="false" max_group="0">
		<text>The rest of the fleet scatters seeing the carnage you've inflicted. You're safe, for now...</text>
		<event load="OPTION_INVALID"/>
	</choice>
	<choice req="cloaking" lvl="3" max_group="998" blue="true" hidden="true">
		<text>(Upgraded Cloaking) Sneak away.</text>
		<event>
			<text>Somehow, despite being cornered by them, your advanced Cloaking lets you disappear and manuever right between the enemy ships. You could probably do something at the beacon without being detected.</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Do something onboard the ship.</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
			<choice>
				<text>Do nothing.</text>
				<event/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice req="TC3_DEAD" lvl="1" hidden="true" blue="false" max_group="998"> <!--prevents the failsafe to force you to select the invalid option-->
		<text>We have nothing to do here...</text>
		<event />
	</choice>
</event>

<event name="ENCOUNTER_TC4">
	<preventQuest/>
	<preventFleet/>
	<aggressive>2</aggressive>
	<text>Hey, there's a second ship here. And it's not hostile. In fact, it's not even a Scrapper. It's a scavenger of some kind, judging by their terribly damaged and dirty hull. Clearly painted as a garbage disposal ship -  but it's way too well-armed to actually be one.</text>
	<beaconType id="map_icon_trash" global="true">
        <color r="110" g="32" b="9" a="1.0"/>
        <unvisitedTooltip>C0ME aND GET It</unvisitedTooltip>
        <visitedTooltip>Explored location. Nothing left of interest.</visitedTooltip>
        <undiscoveredTooltip>W3 ArE HeRE StILL</undiscoveredTooltip>
    </beaconType>
	<choice req="TC4_DEAD" lvl="0" hidden="true" blue="false" max_group="0">
		<text>Try to intervene.</text>
		<event>
			<text>You receive a transmission from the Kestrel. A protogen appears on the communications console. "I'm TRACKER, Federation pilot. Pleased to meet you and everything. These bast- I mean, rude fellows are trying to kill us, and I don't know how much longer we'll hold. Help. I will make sure you get proper compens-CHEESE WE LOST THE LEFT AFTERBURNER, GET TO FIXING IT NOW!"</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Help TRACKER!</text>
				<event>
					<text>The strange lanius ship descends in your view once again (how does it keep coming back?) and prepares to end you once and for all. Despite being hit, TRACKER's ship is still in the fight too! Things are getting serious.</text>
					<ship load="TC_TRASH_COMPACTOR4" hostile="true"/>
					<playMusic>tc_fight</playMusic>
					<environment type="PDS" target="enemy"/>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Let's do this.</text>
						<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice>
				<text>Help the Scrappers!</text>
				<event>
					<text>"Hey, what have WE done to deserve this? Ah, right, I remember now. So be it." As the protogen closes the communication and powers up all of his ship's weapons, you prepare to fight them.</text>
					<ship load="TC_TRASH_MINER" hostile="true"/>
					<playMusic>tc_fight</playMusic>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Let's hope the Scrapper don't attack us after this.</text>
						<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice req="TC4_DEAD" lvl="1" hidden="true" blue="false" max_group="0">
		<text>The Scrap Transmitter's lights flicker wildly. It seems that it's receiving a massive signal... It was a trap all along. It's acting as a multiversal lure, trying to bring even more Scrappers on your location... Interesting, maybe the hunters will soon become the hunted.</text>
		<event load="OPTION_INVALID"/>
	</choice>
	<choice req="pilot" lvl="1" max_group="998" blue="false" hidden="true">
		<text>Let's blow this popsicle stand.</text>
		<event>
			<text>It seems that TRACKER is... dealing with the problem, somehow. You manage to leave them fight.</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Do something onboard the ship.</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
			<choice>
				<text>Do nothing.</text>
				<event/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	</event>

<event name="ENCOUNTER_TC5">
	<preventQuest/>
	<preventFleet/>
	<aggressive>2</aggressive>
	<text>This one's stronger. Faster. Better. Shiny, even. Let's reduce them to dust.</text>
	<beaconType id="map_icon_trash" global="true">
        <color r="110" g="32" b="9" a="1.0"/>
        <unvisitedTooltip>C0ME aND GET It</unvisitedTooltip>
        <visitedTooltip>Explored location. Nothing left of interest.</visitedTooltip>
        <undiscoveredTooltip>W3 ArE HeRE StILL</undiscoveredTooltip>
    </beaconType>
	<ship load="TC_TRASH_COMPACTOR5" hostile="false"/>
	<choice req="TC5_DEAD" lvl="0" hidden="true" blue="false" max_group="0">
		<text>Attack.</text>
		<event>
			<text>We've got lock-on, fire up all weapons!</text>
			<ship hostile="true"/>
			<playMusic>tc_fight</playMusic>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Attack!</text>
				<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice req="TC5_DEAD" lvl="1" hidden="true" blue="false" max_group="0">
		<text>The Scrap Transmitter is audibly groaning, like a ship being torn apart. You've heard a lot of that recently. Maybe you can set one last trap...</text>
		<event load="OPTION_INVALID"/>
	</choice>
	<choice req="pilot" lvl="1" max_group="998" blue="false" hidden="true">
		<text>This one's different - common logic dictates that it's stronger. Let's run.</text>
		<event>
			<text>Somehow, you manage to sneak away. Or perhaps it's sparing you? Strange... You don't have too much time to dwell on it, however.</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Do something onboard the ship.</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
			<choice>
				<text>Do nothing.</text>
				<event/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	</event>

	<event name="ENCOUNTER_TC6">
		<preventQuest/>
	<preventFleet/>
	<aggressive>2</aggressive>
		<text>This is the first Trash Compactor. The prince of the Scrappers, the Trash Eater, is here. His conquest to take over the world starts with your ship. Let's make sure his plans crash and burn.</text>
		<beaconType id="map_icon_trash" global="true">
			<color r="110" g="32" b="9" a="1.0"/>
			<unvisitedTooltip>C0ME aND GET It</unvisitedTooltip>
			<visitedTooltip>Explored location. Nothing left of interest.</visitedTooltip>
			<undiscoveredTooltip>W3 ArE HeRE StILL</undiscoveredTooltip>
		</beaconType>
		<ship load="TC_TRASH_COMPACTOR6" hostile="false"/>
		<choice req="TC6_DEAD" lvl="0" hidden="true" blue="false" max_group="0">
			<text>Attack.</text>
			<event>
				<text>The Universe 0 version of the Scrapper ship is the strongest enemy you've faced so far. You will not survive. Good luck.</text>
				<ship hostile="true"/>
				<playMusic>tc_fight</playMusic>
				<choice hidden="true">
					<text>...</text>
					<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
				</choice>
			</event>
		</choice>
		<choice req="TC6_DEAD" lvl="1" hidden="true" blue="false" max_group="0">
			<text>This is over. Finally. The last Scrapper is fully silent. You feel as if you've saved plenty of renegades from these guys. You're not sure what their plan was - if they even had a plan in the first place.</text>
			<event load="OPTION_INVALID"/>
		</choice>
		<choice req="pilot" lvl="1" max_group="998" blue="false" hidden="true">
			<text>We can't do this.</text>
			<event>
				<text>You manage to leave; you're not exactly sure how.</text>
				<choice>
					<text>Do something onboard the ship.</text>
					<event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
				</choice>
				<choice>
					<text>Do nothing.</text>
					<event/>
				</choice>
			</event>
		</choice>
	</event>


	<ship name="TC_TRASH_COMPACTOR_ROSEGOLD" auto_blueprint="TC_TRASH_COMPACTOR_ROSEGOLD">
	    <ship hostile="true"/>
		<destroyed load="TC_ROSEGOLD_DESTROY"/>
		<deadCrew load="TC_ROSEGOLD_DESTROY"/>
	</ship>

	<event name="ENCOUNTER_TC_ROSEGOLD">
		<preventQuest/>
	<preventFleet/>
	<aggressive>2</aggressive>
		<text>You've arrived at the coordinates and see yet another Scrapper ship. This one is different, your sensors detect weird readings.</text>
		<beaconType id="map_icon_trash" global="true">
			<color r="254" g="190" b="242" a="1"/>
			<unvisitedTooltip>C0ME aND GET It</unvisitedTooltip>
			<visitedTooltip>Explored location. Nothing left of interest.</visitedTooltip>
			<undiscoveredTooltip>W3 ArE HeRE StILL</undiscoveredTooltip>
		</beaconType>
		<ship load="TC_TRASH_COMPACTOR_ROSEGOLD" hostile="false"/>
		<choice req="tc_rosegold_defeated" lvl="0" hidden="true" blue="false" max_group="0">
			<text>Hail them.</text>
			<event>
				<text>They transmit a message. Then they send it again. And again. The same signal repeats endlessly, echoing across every channel on your ship. The message contains only two words, "J0In US". As the message continues to loop, the Scrapper ship powers on it's weapons.</text>
				<ship hostile="true"/>
				<playMusic>tc_fight</playMusic>
				<choice hidden="true">
					<text>Prepare for battle!</text>
					<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
				</choice>
			</event>
		</choice>
		<choice req="tc_rosegold_defeated" lvl="1" hidden="true" blue="false" max_group="0">
			<text>No do-overs.</text>
			<event load="OPTION_INVALID"/>
		</choice>
		<choice req="pilot" lvl="1" max_group="998" blue="false" hidden="true">
			<text>Attempt to sneak away from the Scrapper.</text>
			<event>
				<text>You manage to leave succesfully, with the opportunity of doing something on-board.</text>
				<choice>
					<text>Do something onboard the ship.</text>
					<event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
				</choice>
				<choice>
					<text>Do nothing.</text>
					<event/>
				</choice>
			</event>
		</choice>
	</event>

	<event name="TC_ROSEGOLD_DESTROY">
		<text>The rosegold ship has been defeated.
			While searching through the remains of the ship, you find a dying member of its crew, clutching an intact weapon it seemingly stripped from right from the hull. It seems like they're nibbling on it.
			You can snatch the weapon from them, take them both with you, or leave them to die.
		</text>
		<playMusic/>
		<variable name="tc_rosegold_defeated" op="set" val="1"/>
		<autoReward level="HIGH">stuff</autoReward>
		<choice>
			<text>Snatch the weapon.</text>
			<event>
				<text>You chose to take the functional weapon, leaving the crew member to its fate.</text>
				<weapon name="TC_SHOTGUN_BATTERY_ROSEGOLD"/>
			</event>
		</choice>
		<choice>
			<text>Allow the crew member to eat the weapon.</text>
			<event>
				<text>You promise the scrapper additional scrap for work and a home onboard a non-destroyed ship. After beaming aboard, they quickly finish the weapon, revitalizing themselves.</text>
				<crewMember amount="1" class="rosegold_scrapper_scavenger_mk2"/>
			</event>
		</choice>
		<choice>
			<text>Spend some extra time salvaging.</text>
				<event>
					<text>You instead spend some extra time salvaging and beam away without looking back.
						The wounded scrapper watches you beam away, who knows if it will live or die floating forever, lost in space wreckage. How rude. 
					</text>
					<item_modify>
						<item type="fuel" min="5" max="10"/>
						<item type="scrap" min="25" max="75"/>
						<item type="drones" min="5" max="10"/>
						<item type="missiles" min="5" max="10"/>
					</item_modify>
				</event>
		</choice>
	</event>

