		</text>
		<playMusic/>
		<variable name="tc_adamantine_defeated" op="set" val="1"/>
		<autoReward level="HIGH">stuff</autoReward>
		<choice>
			<text>Snatch the weapon.</text>
			<event>
				<text>You chose to take the functional weapon, leaving the crew member to its fate.</text>
				<drone name="TC_COMBAT_UNSTABLE_ADAMANTINE"/>
			</event>
		</choice>
		<choice>
			<text>Allow the crew member to eat the weapon.</text>
			<event>
				<text>You promise the scrapper additional scrap for work and a home onboard a non-destroyed ship. After beaming aboard, they quickly finish the weapon, revitalizing themselves.</text>
				<crewMember amount="1" class="adamantine_scrapper_heavy_soldier_mk2"/>
			</event>
		</choice>
		<choice>
			<text>Spend some extra time salvaging.</text>
				<event>
					<text>You instead spend some extra time salvaging and beam away without looking back.
						The wounded scrapper watches you beam away, who knows if it will live or die floating forever, lost in space wreckage. How rude. 
					</text>
					<item_modify>
						<item type="fuel" min="5" max="10"/>
						<item type="scrap" min="25" max="75"/>
						<item type="drones" min="5" max="10"/>
						<item type="missiles" min="5" max="10"/>
					</item_modify>
				</event>
		</choice>
	</event>

	<ship name="TC_TRASH_COMPACTOR_ZOG_FIRST" auto_blueprint="TC_SCRAPPER_ZOG">
	    <ship hostile="true"/>
		<destroyed load="TC_ZOG_SKIP"/>
		<deadCrew load="TC_ZOG_SKIP"/>
	</ship>

	<event name="TC_ZOG_SKIP">
		<text>How the hell did you do that.</text>
	</event>
	
	<event name="ENCOUNTER_TC_ZOG">
		<preventQuest/>
	<preventFleet/>
	<aggressive>2</aggressive>
		<text>Your systems go on high alert as your arrival is met with a massive Lanius ship, its weapons raised and charging!</text>
		<beaconType text="YOUR DESTINATION" global="true">
			<color r="255" g="255" b="255" a="1"/>
			<unvisitedTooltip>I am waiting.</unvisitedTooltip>
			<visitedTooltip>We are finished.</visitedTooltip>
			<undiscoveredTooltip>I am waiting.</undiscoveredTooltip>
		</beaconType>
		<variable name="tc_zog_met" op="set" val="1"/>
		<ship load="TC_TRASH_COMPACTOR_ZOG_FIRST" hostile="true"/>
		<status type="limit" target="enemy" system="teleporter" amount="0"/>
		<status type="limit" target="enemy" system="cloaking" amount="0"/>
		<status type="limit" target="enemy" system="mind" amount="0"/>
		<status type="limit" target="enemy" system="drones" amount="0"/>
		<triggeredEvent event="ENCOUNTER_TC_ZOG_CONTINUE" time="4" clearOnJump="true"/>
		<playMusic>tc_fight</playMusic>
		<choice>
			<text>No time to prepare!</text>
			<event/>
		</choice>
	</event>

	<event name="ENCOUNTER_TC_ZOG_CONTINUE">
		<ship hostile="false"/>
		<status type="clear" target="enemy" system="teleporter" amount="100"/>
		<status type="clear" target="enemy" system="cloaking" amount="100"/>
		<status type="clear" target="enemy" system="mind" amount="100"/>
		<status type="clear" target="enemy" system="drones" amount="100"/>
		<text>The Lanius' offensive systems all power down in an instant, and you're met with a hail. On screen comes a featureless Lanius, covered by a shimmering prismatic bubble. 
"Apologies, I'm merely fascinated by first impressions." Its body flexes in manner similar to chuckling, as it logs something into its console.</text>
		<choice>
			<text>What? You did all that just to get a reaction out of me?</text>
			<event>
				<text>As best as you can tell, a bemused expression encroaches the lanius' lack of a face. "To a degree... yes, though the exact reasons are a touch more esoteric..." It paces around their helm for a moment, before jerking their attention back to you.
"Right, my manners, I've misplaced them." They give a small bow before standing upright, arms spread wide in an assumedly welcoming gesture. "I am The Architect, creator and caretaker of the Scrappers." Their arms fall to their sides, posture relaxing. 
"They are as aged as the Lanius, and have grown quite varied across the Multiverse." A fleet of Scrapper Cruisers blip into view, behind the Architect's. </text>
				<choice>
					<text>So... why am I here?</text>
					<event>
						<text>"Succinctly, your exceptional capabilities. Your victories against my older creations are no small feat, even with the assistance of compatriots."</text>
						<choice>
							<text>Do you mean the Trash Compactor?</text>
							<event>
								<text>"Indeed. My more recent creations, the Elemental Scrappers, were an escalation worth testing against you. Granted, most are overly narrow in scope, yet I see such merit in perfecting a purpose. What do you see in them?"</text>
								<choice>
									<text>Elegance, if I had to put it into one word.</text>
									<event>
										<text>They bask in the moment, proud of such high praise for their work. "You elate me so, thank you."</text>
										<choice>
											<text>Continue...</text>
											<event load="ENCOUNTER_TC_ZOG_CHOICE"/>
										</choice>
									</event>
								</choice>
								<choice>
									<text>Most are good, but some could definitely do with some work.</text>
									<event>
										<text>"I appreciate the earnesty, as perfection does not come without error."</text>
										<choice>
											<text>Continue...</text>
											<event load="ENCOUNTER_TC_ZOG_CHOICE"/>
										</choice>
									</event>
								</choice>
								<choice>
									<text>I've seen better.</text>
									<event>
										<text>"... Duly noted..."</text>
										<choice>
											<text>Continue...</text>
											<event load="ENCOUNTER_TC_ZOG_CHOICE"/>
										</choice>
									</event>
								</choice>
							</event>
						</choice>
					</event>
				</choice>
			</event>
		</choice>
	</event>

	<ship name="TC_TRASH_COMPACTOR_MERGED_AG" auto_blueprint="TC_TRASH_COMPACTOR_MERGED_AG">
	    <ship hostile="true"/>
		<destroyed load="TC_MERGED_DESTROY"/>
		<deadCrew load="TC_MERGED_DESTROY"/>
	</ship>

	<ship name="TC_TRASH_COMPACTOR_MERGED_GR" auto_blueprint="TC_TRASH_COMPACTOR_MERGED_GR">
	    <ship hostile="true"/>
		<destroyed load="TC_MERGED_DESTROY"/>
		<deadCrew load="TC_MERGED_DESTROY"/>
	</ship>

	<ship name="TC_TRASH_COMPACTOR_MERGED_RA" auto_blueprint="TC_TRASH_COMPACTOR_MERGED_RA">
	    <ship hostile="true"/>
		<destroyed load="TC_MERGED_DESTROY"/>
		<deadCrew load="TC_MERGED_DESTROY"/>
	</ship>

	<event name="ENCOUNTER_TC_ZOG_CHOICE">
		<text>Righting themselves, the Architect refocuses on you once more. "In any case, I've one more design of my creation in need of a proper test. Yes, there is indeed a reward awaiting you, should you succeed. Would you honor me so?"</text>
		<choice>
			<text>Agree.</text>
			<event>
				<text>"Which pairing intrigues you most?"</text>
				<choice>
					<text>Adamantine + Golden.</text>
					<event>
						<text>The Architect's ship moves away to a safer distance and one of the Scrapper ships moves to engage.</text>
						<ship load="TC_TRASH_COMPACTOR_MERGED_AG" hostile="true"/>
						<triggeredEvent event="POWER_SURGE_ROSEGOLD" loops="999999999" thisFight="true" time="20">
							<warningMessage id="warning_power_surge_rosegold" x="692" y="84" time="5.0" r="255" g="181" b="225" centerText="true" flash="true" sound="surgeWarning" useWarningLine="true"/>
						</triggeredEvent>
						<choice>
							<text>Continue...</text>
							<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
						</choice>
					</event>
				</choice>
				<choice>
					<text>Golden + Rosegold.</text>
					<event>
						<text>The Architect's ship moves away to a safer distance and one of the Scrapper ships in the distance moves to engage.</text>
						<ship load="TC_TRASH_COMPACTOR_MERGED_GR" hostile="true"/>
						<triggeredEvent event="POWER_SURGE_ADAMANTINE" loops="999999999" thisFight="true" time="20">
							<warningMessage id="warning_power_surge_adamantine" x="692" y="84" time="5.0" r="120" g="36" b="65" centerText="true" flash="true" sound="surgeWarning" useWarningLine="true"/>
						</triggeredEvent>
						<choice>
							<text>Continue...</text>
							<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
						</choice>
					</event>
				</choice>
				<choice>
					<text>Rosegold + Adamantine.</text>
					<event>
						<text>The Architect's ship moves away to a safer distance and one of the Scrapper ships in the distance moves to engage.</text>
						<ship load="TC_TRASH_COMPACTOR_MERGED_RA" hostile="true"/>
						<triggeredEvent event="POWER_SURGE_GOLDEN" loops="999999999" thisFight="true" time="20">
							<warningMessage id="warning_power_surge_golden" x="692" y="84" time="5.0" r="255" g="201" b="5" centerText="true" flash="true" sound="surgeWarning" useWarningLine="true"/>
						</triggeredEvent>
						<choice>
							<text>Continue...</text>
							<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
						</choice>
					</event>
				</choice>
			</event>
		</choice>
		<choice>
			<text>Decline.</text>
			<event>
				<text>You're met with a long pause, and a creeping sense of disappointment. A low nod escapes the Architect. "Very well. That will be the end of our interactions." Their ship jumps away, the fleet of Scrappers soon following after.</text>
				<instantEscape/>
				<choice hidden="true">
					<text>Do something onboard the ship.</text>
					<event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
				</choice>
				<choice hidden="true">
					<text>Do nothing.</text>
					<event/>
				</choice>
			</event>
		</choice>
	</event>

	<event name="TC_MERGED_DESTROY">
		<item_modify>
			<item type="scrap" min="100" max="100"/>
		</item_modify>
		<playMusic/>
		<text>As the Scrapper splits into debris, the Architect's vessel emerges. "A wonderfully executed battle, congratulations. As promised, your reward." </text>
		<choice>
			<text>That's it? Just one last fight and we're done?</text>
			<event>
				<text>The Architect pauses in their tracks, facing you once more. A suggestion of confusion upon their blank visage is met with an inquisitively raised hand. "I had not expected such gumption from you, yet perhaps that much should have been readily apparent. Your attempts to even reach me in such a way is already extraordinary on its own..." 
They mumble to themselves, pacing back and forth as they ponder your response. All at once, it dawns on them.
"Ah. You desire challenge, do you not? And perhaps further reward for such monumental effort?"</text>
				<choice>
					<text>Send me your strongest.</text>
					<event>
						<instantEscape/>
						<variable name="tc_zog_met" op="set" val="2"/>
						<text>They give that same chuckle-like gesture, stance postured for dramatics. "I shall do you one better. Me. I am to be your final opponent, with no quarter given." They relax, just a touch. "I have never truly tested my own design's efficacy. This would be a grand experiment for both of us. I trust you will have no difficulty finding me once more. I'll be waiting." 
The Architect's ship jumps away. Their vessel leaves a quickly fading shimmer in the space it once occupied.</text>
					</event>
				</choice>
				<choice>
					<text>On second thought, I'm good. </text>
					<event>
						<instantEscape/>
						<text>The Architect nods. "Very well. You've performed more than admirably so far. I shant take more of your time. I wish you well with your mission." The Architect's ship jumps away. Their vessel leaves a quickly fading shimmer in the space it once occupied.</text>
					</event>
				</choice>
			</event>
		</choice>
	</event>

