	<event name="TC_ZOG_DESTROY">
		<text>As the Architect's ship shatters into countless shards, you hear them teleport beside you. "Wonderful! Truly, wonderfully done! I could not execute a better performance myself." You catch them staring out towards the wreckage of their cruiser. 
"Much as I adored my design, its destruction only shows its imperfection. Now I've the perfect opportunity to perfect it." You catch what might be a smile on their faceless face. They shake their head a touch, turning to you.
"Right, your reward! I would hope that you find the selections on offer sufficient for your purposes. Though, if you'd kindly, only take one." </text>
		<metaVariable name="tc_quest2_completed" op="set" val="1"/>
		<variable name="tc_zog_met" op="set" val="3"/>
		<playMusic/>
		<choice>
			<text>Omega Amalgam Flak.</text>
			<event>
				<text>"It's a miracle this weapon doesn't tear itself apart while firing. If memory serves me, its constructed of... platinum, iridium, and osmium, as you might call them."</text>
				<weapon name="TC_SHOTGUN_OMEGA"/>
				<choice hidden="true">
					<text>Continue...</text>
					<event load="TC_ZOG_ACCOMPANY"/>
				</choice>
			</event>
		</choice>
		<choice>
			<text>Midnight Prismatic Flak.</text>
			<event>
				<text>"Many disparate ideas fueled this weapon, and I simply couldn't decide on just one."</text>
				<weapon name="TC_SHOTGUN_MIDNIGHT"/>
				<choice hidden="true">
					<text>Continue...</text>
					<event load="TC_ZOG_ACCOMPANY"/>
				</choice>
			</event>
		</choice>
		<choice>
			<text>Elemental Toggle Flak.</text>
			<event>
				<text>"The Toggle Flak is already a joy to behold, yet I saw to it that it should reach even higher potentials."</text>
				<weapon name="TC_SHOTGUN_TOGGLE_ROSEGOLD"/>
				<choice hidden="true">
					<text>Continue...</text>
					<event load="TC_ZOG_ACCOMPANY"/>
				</choice>
			</event>
		</choice>
		<choice>
			<text>Scrapper Synthesiser.</text>
			<event>
				<text>"My creations are quite adept at self replication, as you've no doubt seen. Though, a helping hand is always appreciated."</text>
				<drone name="TC_DRONE_SCRAPPER_SYNTHESISER"/>
				<choice hidden="true">
					<text>Continue...</text>
					<event load="TC_ZOG_ACCOMPANY"/>
				</choice>
			</event>
		</choice>
		<choice>
			<text>Scrap Duplicator.</text>
			<event>
				<text>"A touch blasé, but I can respect the desire for scrap."</text>
				<augment name="SCRAP_DUPLICATOR"/>
				<choice hidden="true">
					<text>Continue...</text>
					<event load="TC_ZOG_ACCOMPANY"/>
				</choice>
			</event>
		</choice>
		<choice>
			<text>Jadesteel Scrapper.</text>
			<event>
				<text>"A Scrapper with limitless potential. I've never had the opportunity to see them at their highest."</text>
				<crewMember amount="1" class="jadesteel_scrapper"/>
				<choice hidden="true">
					<text>Continue...</text>
					<event load="TC_ZOG_ACCOMPANY"/>
				</choice>
			</event>
		</choice>
	</event>

	<event name="TC_ZOG_ACCOMPANY">
		<text>"What good is an additional field test without proper documentation? I will accompany you for as long as I am able, so that I may see it to its end."
		
			[Elemental Scrapper enhancements permanently unlocked! You can find it in the Scrapper lab.]
			[More blueprints available in the Compactor!]
		</text>
		<crewMember amount="1" class="unique_zog" all_skills="2">Zog</crewMember>
		<jumpEvent name="ZOG_CHECK">ZOG_CHECKER</jumpEvent>
		<unlockCustomShip>PLAYER_SHIP_ELEMENTAL</unlockCustomShip>
		<achievement silent="false">ACH_TCC_ZOGDEFEAT</achievement>
		<choice>
			<text>Continue...</text>
			<event/>
		</choice>
	</event>
		
